Problem on Averages-6 - Placement Exercise
NOTE: This kind of question is very common in campus placement ( TCS, Wipro, etc.) 
because it makes the use of average and some basic logic.

Problem:
The average temperature of a week was calculated as 32Â°C. 
Later, it was realized that the temperature of Monday was taken as 30Â°C instead of 16Â°C.
Find the correct average temperature of the week.

Solution: 
Note: Formula of Average = Sum of observations / No. of observations.
      Sum of observations = Average X No. of observations

Here No. of observations is No. of days in week = 7
Average = 32
Original total sum = 7 Ã— 32 = 224

Temperature was taken as 30Â°C instead of 16Â°C 
Error = 30 âˆ’ 16 = 14
It means 14Â°C is the error that needs to be subtracted from the sum.
Correct total sum of temperature = 224 âˆ’ 14 = 210

Correct average = 210 Ã· 7 = 30 âœ…

Final Answer
ğŸ‘ The correct average temperature of the week = 30Â°C
